body: "Domain-by-domain SDK promotion under pm-usfg covers read (pm-rjqr), lifecycle (pm-98cz), schema/config/profile (pm-3mna), history maintenance (pm-4a7m), plan (pm-je50), governance/health/gc (pm-oxrw), annotations (pm-zwpp), and execution (pm-oslr) — but nobody owns the package/extension platform family. The universal-tool story (pm-w89s, exemplar pm-cbwg) requires an SDK-built PM tool to install and manage packages without shelling to the CLI. Promote the install/upgrade/extension lifecycle logic (multi-target install aggregation, managed-extensions.json state, activation) behind typed SDK primitives, and align with the CLI-side consolidation pm-tnud so the noun rename and the SDK promotion do not conflict."
